Description: Part of a jar-seal: of grey clay, with an impressed inscription of the name of Khasekhem. This fragment is in good condition.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, pl.XXII, 197; H. R. Hall, 'Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs etc. in the British Museum: Volume 1 : Royal scarabs' (London, 1913), 289, no.2767; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.83, abb.313; see also vols. I, 161 and II, 855, n. 987; 1136.
